Voice-call additions (this fork)
--------------------------------
This fork adds Session-to-Session voice-call support. The added calls/
package (introduced on the feat/voice-calls* branches) is licensed
AGPL-3.0-or-later and contains code ported — as direct ports, not a
clean-room reimplementation — from Session Foundation's official
clients, with attribution and preserved copyright headers:

  - session-android (GPLv3)  — state machine, signaling processor, peer
    connection config, wire message model
  - session-desktop (AGPLv3) — TypeScript call engine, outgoing/incoming
    call message handling

Per-file porting provenance is recorded in calls/COPYING.provenance.

Closed-group additions (this fork)
----------------------------------
The groups/ package (@session.js/groups, branch feat/closed-groups) adds
legacy closed-group support (05-prefixed groups) and is licensed
AGPL-3.0-or-later. It contains code ported — as direct ports, not a
clean-room reimplementation — from the same Session Foundation clients:

  - session-desktop (AGPLv3) — group lifecycle, inbound control dispatch,
    group decryption, polling model
  - session-android (GPLv3)  — group update handling, formation, polling

Per-file provenance is recorded in groups/COPYING.provenance; the plan and
verified protocol facts live in docs/closed-groups/IMPLEMENTATION.md. The
core-client patches it relies on (GroupPoller + Session.addGroupPoller,
sendGroupMessage / sendClosedGroupUpdate / sendConfigurationMessage,
sealKeypairWrapper / openKeypairWrapper, the ./crypto export, the
ClosedGroupControlMessage schema/mapper + groupUpdate/syncClosedGroups
events, and the decryptForClosedGroup fix) are written fresh from the
published proto facts, Copyright (c) 2026 AdnaneKhan, and remain
MIT-licensable for upstream contribution.

The combined work (forked client plus calls/ and groups/ packages) is
distributed under the terms of the GNU Affero General Public License
version 3 (AGPLv3); GPLv3 Android code combines into an AGPLv3 work per
AGPLv3 §13.

Fresh-written core-client patches
---------------------------------
The following patches to the core client are written fresh from the
published SessionProtos.proto field facts (no lines copied from GPL/AGPL
sources), Copyright (c) 2026 AdnaneKhan, and remain MIT-licensable for
contribution upstream to MIT session.js: the mapCallMessage mapper fix,
the CallMessage schema class, Session.prototype.sendCallMessage,
setPollInterval, and NetworkNode (voice calls); and, for closed groups, the
./crypto export, the decryptForClosedGroup fix, GroupPoller,
Session.addGroupPoller/removeGroupPoller, sendGroupMessage,
sendClosedGroupUpdate, sendConfigurationMessage, sealKeypairWrapper,
openKeypairWrapper, the ClosedGroupControlMessage schema + mapClosedGroup-
ControlMessage mapper + groupUpdate/syncClosedGroups events, GroupContext in
visible sends, and the 30-day ConfigurationMessage TTL.

AGPL §13 — network-use obligation
---------------------------------
Anyone running this code (original + voice-call additions) as a network
service must make the Corresponding Source of the running version
available to users of that service, under the terms of the AGPLv3.
To satisfy this: these repositories are kept public, and releases are
tagged and archived. Service operators embedding this library inherit the
same obligation.

